  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\"><img alt=\"House Towers of Harrenhal.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/50px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/75px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/100px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Walton Towers</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\"><img alt=\"House Towers of Harrenhal.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/50px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/75px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5a/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg/100px-House_Towers_of_Harrenhal.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Walton_Towers_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Walton Towers (The Rise of the Dragon).jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/dd/Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/300px-Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"399\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/dd/Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/450px-Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/dd/Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/600px-Walton_Towers_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Ser Walton Towers in the melee for Harrenhal by Sven Sauer and Igor Posavec for <i>The Rise of the Dragon</i> ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\">House Towers</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/44_AC\" title=\"44 AC\">44&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Jordan_Towers\" title=\"Jordan Towers\">Jordan Towers</a></li><li>Other son(s)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sons_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Sons of the Dragon\">The Sons of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Walton Towers</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Household_knight\" title=\"Household knight\">household knight</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>, rising to be the short-lived <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a> and the founder of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\">House Towers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Walton_Towers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a> wiped out <a href=\"/index.php/House_Harroway\" title=\"House Harroway\">House Harroway</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/44_AC\" title=\"44 AC\">44&#160;AC</a>, he grew weary of the ambitious king's men entreating him for the lordship of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>. Instead, Maegor decreed that the strongest of his <a href=\"/index.php/Household_knight\" title=\"Household knight\">household knights</a> would have Harrenhal. Ser Walton was one of twenty-three knights of the king's household who fought in the blood-soaked streets of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Harroway%27s_Town\" title=\"Lord Harroway&#39;s Town\">Lord Harroway's Town</a> for the prize. Though gravely wounded in the melee, Walton emerged victorious and was named <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a>, though its domains were much diminished as the Harroway holdings held separately from Harrenhal were granted to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alton_Butterwell\" title=\"Alton Butterwell\">Alton Butterwell</a> and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Darnold_Darry\" title=\"Darnold Darry\">Darnold Darry</a>. Walton did not live long enough to enjoy his lordship, as he died within a fortnight from the wounds he had taken in gaining his prize, and Harrenhal subsequently passed to Walton's eldest son, <a href=\"/index.php/Jordan_Towers\" title=\"Jordan Towers\">Jordan Towers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>House Towers was the fourth house to rule Harrenhal, but Walton's line faltered after only two generations and died with <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_Towers\" title=\"Maegor Towers\">his grandson</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/61_AC\" title=\"61 AC\">61&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Walton_Towers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" bor